description: This classic pale ale boasts a light, hazy amber colour thats pleasing to the eye. Back when prawn cocktails were fine dining and lapels were big enough to take an eye out, beer in a can was called a Tinnie. From simpler times comes the inspiration for this modern beer with a classic Aussie name. Cheers mate! Awards: World's Best Pale Bitter in the 4.5% to 5.5% category at the World Beer Awards 2019. This special distillation process is a closely guarded secret, known only to a handful of people.
